For every class, a separate `siswa.findMany` query runs:

```typescript
const kelasList = await prisma.kelas.findMany(...);  // 1 query
const perKelas = await Promise.all(
  kelasList.map(async (k) => {
    const ids = (await prisma.siswa.findMany({   // ← N queries, one per class
      where: { kelasId: k.id }, select: { id: true }
    })).map(s => s.id);
    const khd = monthlyKehadiran.filter(h => ids.includes(h.siswaId));
    // ...
  })
);
```

**Fix**: Use `groupBy` in a single query, or batch all student IDs by kelasId with one query + `Map`:

```typescript
const allStudents = await prisma.siswa.findMany({
  select: { id: true, kelasId: true }
});
const studentMap = new Map<string, string[]>();
for (const s of allStudents) {
  const arr = studentMap.get(s.kelasId) ?? [];
  arr.push(s.id);
  studentMap.set(s.kelasId, arr);
}
// Now use studentMap.get(k.id) — zero extra DB queries
```

