```typescript
// 5 full-array iterations for what one pass does
const totalHadir = monthlyKehadiran.filter(k => k.status === 'HADIR').length;
const totalIzin  = monthlyKehadiran.filter(k => k.status === 'IZIN').length;
const totalSakit = monthlyKehadiran.filter(k => k.status === 'SAKIT').length;
const totalPkl   = monthlyKehadiran.filter(k => k.status === 'PKL').length;
const totalAlpa  = monthlyKehadiran.filter(k => k.status === 'ALPA').length;
```

**Fix**: Single pass with `reduce`:

```typescript
const counts = monthlyKehadiran.reduce((acc, k) => {
  if (k.status === 'HADIR') acc.hadir++;
  else if (k.status === 'IZIN') acc.izin++;
  else if (k.status === 'SAKIT') acc.sakit++;
  else if (k.status === 'PKL') acc.pkl++;
  else if (k.status === 'ALPA') acc.alpa++;
  return acc;
}, { hadir: 0, izin: 0, sakit: 0, pkl: 0, alpa: 0 });
```

The sort runs **twice** every render — once for desktop table, once for mobile cards:

```tsx
// Line 221 + 230 — identical sort, two new arrays
{[...students].sort((a, b) => ...).map(s => <tr>...</tr>)}
{[...students].sort((a, b) => ...).map(s => <div>...</div>)}
```

**Fix**: Memoize:

```typescript
const sortedStudents = useMemo(() =>
  [...students].sort((a, b) => sortMode === 'abjad'
    ? a.nama.localeCompare(b.nama, 'id')
    : (parseInt(a.nis)||0) - (parseInt(b.nis)||0)),
  [students, sortMode]
);
```

---

Every route handler disables caching. No data is ever reused. Specific candidates:

| Route | Cache Strategy | Rationale |
|-------|---------------|-----------|
| `/api/admin/stats` | SWR 60s | Monthly aggregates don't need sub-minute freshness |
| `/api/admin/classes` | SWR 300s | Classes change only when admin adds/edits one |
| `/api/recap/daily` | SWR 30s | Same date queried by multiple teachers |
| `/api/recap/*` (historical) | SWR 120s | Past dates never change |

**Example for stats:**

```typescript
// ponytail: SWR via Next.js segment config, freshness ≥60s for aggregate data
export const revalidate = 60;
// Remove: export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic';
```

```typescript
const fetchData = async () => {
  const statsRes = await fetch('/api/admin/stats');   // wait...
  const statsData = await statsRes.json();
  setStats(statsData);
  const appRes = await fetch('/api/admin/approval');  // ...then this
  // ...
};
```

These two endpoints are independent. Sequential waiting adds ~2× latency to page load.

**Fix**: Parallel with `Promise.all`:

```typescript
const [statsRes, appRes] = await Promise.all([
  fetch('/api/admin/stats'),
  fetch('/api/admin/approval'),
]);
```

```typescript
const loginAttempts = new Map<string, { count: number; resetTime: number }>();
```

Each unique IP adds an entry that lives for up to 15 minutes. **No cleanup mechanism.** With 1000 unique IPs/hour, the Map holds 1000 entries permanently (each expires after 15 min but is never deleted).

**Fix**: Add periodic cleanup or use a `Map` with a max-size eviction:

```typescript
// Simple TTL sweep — run every 5 minutes
const CLEANUP_INTERVAL = 5 * 60 * 1000;
if (loginAttempts.size > 1000) {
  const now = Date.now();
  for (const [ip, entry] of loginAttempts) {
    if (now > entry.resetTime) loginAttempts.delete(ip);
  }
}
```

`AttendanceForm.tsx:66` reads uploaded images as base64 data URLs and stores them in component state (`buktiPreview`). With a full class of ~30 students each uploading a 1-2MB photo, the component holds **~45-60MB of base64 strings** in memory until the user navigates away.

**Fix**: Use `URL.createObjectURL()` instead (blob URLs that don't encode to base64), and revoke when done:

```typescript
const previewUrl = URL.createObjectURL(file);
// store previewUrl in state
// ... cleanup on unmount or when preview replaced:
useEffect(() => {
  return () => { if (previewUrl) URL.revokeObjectURL(previewUrl); };
}, [previewUrl]);
```

